&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Opportunity: Additive Manufacturing Engineering Manager with Formative 3D in Falls Church, VA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a hands‑on leader with deep expertise in large‑format additive manufacturing and extrusion‑based processes? Do you enjoy building teams, optimizing production systems, and solving complex print challenges in real time? Are you excited to help scale a cutting‑edge 3D printing operation and shape the future of manufacturing? If you answered yes, we want to speak with you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Additive Manufacturing Engineering Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you will lead both the strategic direction and day‑to‑day execution of our additive manufacturing operations. This role blends leadership, technical expertise, and operational ownership—guiding production while advancing the next generation of processes, systems, and capabilities. You’ll work closely across engineering, production, and leadership teams to ensure efficient, scalable manufacturing while driving continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop a team of LFAM/FDM technicians, promoting safety, accountability, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own print processes and optimization, including parameters, material flow, toolpaths, and part quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot production issues (e.g., delamination, warping, equipment faults) and implement corrective actions quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Production to streamline post-processing and assembly workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage capacity planning, scheduling, and staffing in coordination with HR.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Engineering and R&amp;amp;D on new materials, processes, and finishing methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive automation and smart factory initiatives across the facility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report to leadership on KPIs, timelines, resource use, and risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain SOPs, ensuring quality, safety, and accurate documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and develop team members through performance management and career growth planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering, Mechatronics, Electrical Engineering, Materials Science, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7-10+ years of manufacturing experience, including hands-on additive manufacturing (LFAM and/or FDM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in extrusion-based printing, including toolpaths, parameter optimization, and pellet/filament material handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with large-format additive systems (e.g., CEAD, Caracol, Thermwood) preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of automation, robotics, and smart factory systems (MES, ERP, IoT).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lean, Six Sigma, or similar experience driving yield improvement, scrap reduction, and cycle time efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead technical teams in fast-paced or startup environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, problem-solving, and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in an industrial environment and use PPE as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Formative 3D?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Built environments can be manufactured the same way the best technology products are: faster, smarter and at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formative 3D deploys full-scale manufacturing solutions built for speed, flexibility and real-world impact. By combining advanced 3D printing, robotics and technology, we rethink how physical products for the built world are created — from concept to installation. We design and manufacture products that

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Opportunity: CNC Operator with Formative 3D in Falls Church, VA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you enjoy working hands‑on with machines, tools, and materials to create high‑quality parts? Are you detail‑oriented and energized by technical craftsmanship in a fast‑paced manufacturing environment? Ready to support innovative production workflows using CNC machining and advanced 3D printing? If so, we’d love to meet you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formative 3D is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;CNC Operator&lt;/strong&gt; to support post‑processing operations and fabricate custom fixtures and jigs that enhance our production workflow. This role blends hands‑on machining with technical precision and close collaboration across production and engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll operate CNC and robotic milling equipment to post‑process large‑format 3D‑printed furniture components while contributing to continuous improvements in efficiency, quality, and shop operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with production and engineering teams to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate 3‑axis CNC routers and 6‑axis robotic milling machines to post‑process 3D‑printed components and produce fixtures and jigs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret technical drawings and CAD files to set up and execute milling operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform post‑processing tasks on printed parts, including trimming, sanding, and surface finishing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect machined and printed parts for dimensional accuracy and quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain, calibrate, and troubleshoot CNC equipment and tooling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering and production teams to improve fixture design and workflow efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with general shop duties, including material preparation, organization, and equipment upkeep&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience operating CNC milling machines in a production or prototyping environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in reading technical drawings and using measurement tools such as calipers and micrometers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with G‑code, CAM software, and CNC setup procedures (Fusion 360 preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong mechanical aptitude and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with post‑processing plastics or composite materials (preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently while contributing to a collaborative team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort lifting up to 50 lbs and working in a hands‑on shop setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with 3D printing or furniture assembly—or a strong desire to learn—is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compensation commensurate with experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full suite of healthcare benefits, including medical, dental, and vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive PTO plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive retirement plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Formative 3D?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Built environments can be manufactured the same way the best technology products are: faster, smarter and at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formative 3D deploys full-scale manufacturing solutions built for speed, flexibility and real-world impact. By combining advanced 3D printing, robotics and technology, we rethink how physical products for the built world are created — from concept to installation. We design and manufacture products that range from high-end furniture systems and architectural lighting to jigs, fixtures, and tooling.&lt;/p&gt;
