&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Opportunity: Cybersecurity Analyst with KPI Solutions in Cincinnati, OH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local candidates only — this is an onsite role in Cincinnati, OH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6-Month Contract-to-Hire | Full-Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for a cybersecurity role where you’re doing more than watching alerts come in? Do you enjoy digging into issues, responding in real time, and finding better ways to keep systems protected? If so, this could be a strong next step.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KPI Solutions is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Cybersecurity Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join their &lt;strong&gt;Cincinnati team onsite&lt;/strong&gt;. In this role, you will take an active role in monitoring, investigating, and responding to security threats while helping strengthen overall security operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join KPI Solutions?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6-month contract-to-hire with opportunity to convert to full-time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on, high-impact role with real ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure across IT, compliance, and security programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to help improve and mature security processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Cybersecurity Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;, you will help protect systems by actively monitoring, investigating, and responding to security events while contributing to long-term improvements in security operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and respond to security alerts across systems and endpoints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate incidents including phishing, account compromise, and suspicious activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support threat analysis, containment, and resolution efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with tools such as SIEM, endpoint security, and email security platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to audit readiness efforts, including SOC 2 support and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and review access controls and user activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support endpoint security, patching, and device compliance tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain email, network, and identity security protection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in security coverage and recommend improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support security awareness efforts and ongoing risk reduction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear documentation, reporting, and incident tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is detail-oriented, proactive, and comfortable working in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, you should have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in cybersecurity, IT security, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with security tools (SIEM, endpoint protection, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong incident investigation and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to respond to and manage security issues independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of security controls, access management, and risk mitigation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with audit or compliance environments (SOC 2 or similar is a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and ability to work across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Need to Know&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Cincinnati, OH (must be local — onsite role)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;/li&gt

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Opportunity: Director of Human Resources with Greenleaf Corporation in Saegertown, PA (near Erie, PA)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for a role where your HR expertise truly matters?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Director of Human Resources&lt;/strong&gt; opportunity allows you to lead HR operations, support the workforce, and partner closely with leadership in a dynamic manufacturing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role blends &lt;strong&gt;strategic HR leadership with day-to-day operational involvement&lt;/strong&gt;, perfect for someone who understands the realities of manufacturing and enjoys being visible and engaged on the floor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to make an immediate impact in a hands-on leadership role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong partnership with site and facility leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contract-to-hire pathway with long-term potential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a stable, established manufacturing organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Responsible For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll own the full HR function at the site level, balancing strategy with execution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead recruitment strategy and hiring for a manufacturing workforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage employee relations, performance management, and workplace concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide disciplinary actions and ensure fair, consistent practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify training needs and implement development programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee compensation and benefits administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with employment laws, policies, and regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain HR documentation, reporting, and HRIS accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and support the HR team, setting clear priorities and direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted HR partner to plant and operational leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of HR experience in a manufacturing environment (required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience handling employee relations and compliance issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SHRM or PHR certification (required)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong HRIS experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage sensitive situations with professionalism and discretion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident, practical leadership style — comfortable making decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, organization, and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Microsoft Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working on-site in an operational setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Greenleaf Corporation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenleaf Corporation is an established manufacturing organization with a strong focus on quality, operational excellence, and continuous improvement. Based in &lt;strong&gt;Saegertown, Pennsylvania (near Erie, PA)&lt;/strong&gt;, Greenleaf supports a skilled workforce in a fast-paced, production-driven environment where collaboration, accountability, and hands-on leadership are valued.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The organization is committed to supporting its employees while driving performance and long-term growth, making HR a critical partner to the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply online today if you’re an experienced HR leader looking for a hands-on, contract-to-hire opportunity where you can make an immediate impact. Qualified candidates will be contacted to discuss next steps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Equal Opportunity Employer (EEO/M/F/D/V) No third‑party candidates, please.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#ZR&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Opportunity: Director of Industrial Design with Formative 3D in Falls Church, VA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you highly skilled in 3D design and CAD, with a strong understanding of DFM/DFA principles? Do you enjoy leading product development, prototyping, and cross‑functional collaboration? Are you excited to shape product strategy, innovation, and long‑term growth through design? If you answered yes, we want to speak with you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Director of Industrial Design&lt;/strong&gt; you will take ownership, think like a builder, and balance creative vision with practical execution. This role requires strong leadership, advanced design expertise, and the ability to move seamlessly from concept development to production problem‑solving while collaborating cross‑functionally to uphold high design and industry standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead near-, mid-, and long‑term design initiatives that inform the product roadmap and expand future opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive rapid, iterative prototyping through sketching, modeling, and physical builds to support discovery and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate design exploration and research into actionable product, R&amp;amp;D, and growth strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and maintain a clear product roadmap with aligned priorities, timelines, and deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the full product development lifecycle from concept through production across multiple concurrent projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering, manufacturing, and client service teams to align design intent with feasibility, cost, and go‑to‑market plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish tools, workflows, and cadences to track progress, improve execution, and manage risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide concept development across furniture, lighting, and emerging built‑environment categories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new opportunities beyond current product lines, including architectural systems and additive-enabled solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit, mentor, and lead a multidisciplinary design team, fostering accountability, curiosity, and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with leadership and external partners to align vision, expand influence, and position design as a strategic driver of the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8-12+ years of industrial design experience bringing complex physical products from concept through production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced expertise in 3D modeling and CAD tools (e.g., SolidWorks, Rhino, Fusion 360).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of DFM/DFA principles and production-ready design documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with additive manufacturing processes and related materials, tolerances, and finishes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead iterative prototyping, testing, and performance validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with parametric or computational design is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to create and manage detailed drawings, specifications, and BOMs for production handoff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
