&lt;p&gt;We’re building the next generation of manufacturing through advanced 3D printing. What begins with furniture and lighting is quickly expanding into a broader ambition: to rethink how the built environment is conceived, designed, and realized. Formative 3D is building a new model of manufacturing for the built environment using advanced 3D printing, robotics, and automation. We design and manufacture products that range from high-end furnitur

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career Opportunity: Director of Programs with EPIC Youth in Columbus, OH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an enthusiastic, hands-on leader who thrives on building meaningful programs, developing strong teams, and creating lasting impact for young people? Do you bring experience in youth development, mentorship, facilitation, and program excellence? Are you energized by the opportunity to coach staff, strengthen program quality, and help youth grow as confident leaders? If so, we want to speak with you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Director of Programs&lt;/strong&gt; provides strategic and hands-on leadership across EPIC Youth’s programs, ensuring high-quality, consistent, and impactful services. This role strengthens program models, supports staff development, and drives continuous improvement in alignment with EPIC Youth’s mission of mentorship, leadership development, trauma-informed practice, and measurable youth outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay range: $65k - $73k; depending on experience and knowledge.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities of the position include:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design, refinement, and implementation of EPIC Youth programs to ensure consistency, effectiveness, and alignment with organizational standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all programs integrate mentorship, leadership development, and skill-building as core strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee quality assurance processes, including curriculum fidelity, facilitation standards, and participant engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure programs reflect best practices in PBIS, social-emotional learning (SEL), trauma-informed care, and positive youth development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development of staff facilitation skills, including group management, public speaking, youth engagement, and culturally responsive instruction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model high-quality facilitation and mentorship through direct engagement as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise Program Managers and support their growth as leaders, facilitators, and mentors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide coaching, feedback, and performance oversight to ensure staff meet EPIC Youth’s expectations for professionalism, relationship-building, and youth impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify training needs and support ongoing staff development in mentorship, behavior support, and leadership instruction.&lt;/li&gt;
